msgid "Return the connection string to connect to the database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.dsn:3
msgid ""
"The string contains all the parameters set to a non-default value, which "
"might come either from the connection string and parameters passed to "
"`~Connection.connect()` or from environment variables. The password is never "
"returned (you can read it using the `password` attribute)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/objects.rst:15
msgid "The `get_parameters()` method returns the same information as a dict."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.status:1
msgid "The status of the connection. See :pq:`PQstatus()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/objects.rst:20
msgid ""
"The status can be one of a number of values. However, only two of these are "
"seen outside of an asynchronous connection procedure: `~pq.ConnStatus.OK` "
"and `~pq.ConnStatus.BAD`. A good connection to the database has the status `!"
"OK`. Ordinarily, an `!OK` status will remain so until `Connection.close()`, "
"but a communications failure might result in the status changing to `!BAD` "
"prematurely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.transaction_status:1
msgid ""
"The current in-transaction status of the session. See :pq:"
"`PQtransactionStatus()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/objects.rst:29
msgid ""
"The status can be `~pq.TransactionStatus.IDLE` (currently idle), `~pq."
"TransactionStatus.ACTIVE` (a command is in progress), `~pq.TransactionStatus."
"INTRANS` (idle, in a valid transaction block), or `~pq.TransactionStatus."
"INERROR` (idle, in a failed transaction block). `~pq.TransactionStatus."
"UNKNOWN` is reported if the connection is bad. `!ACTIVE` is reported only "
"when a query has been sent to the server and not yet completed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.pipeline_status:1
msgid ""
"The current pipeline status of the client. See :pq:`PQpipelineStatus()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.backend_pid:1
msgid ""
"The process ID (PID) of the backend process handling this connection. See :"
"pq:`PQbackendPID()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.vendor:1
msgid "A string representing the database vendor connected to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/objects.rst:42
msgid ""
"Normally it is `PostgreSQL`; it may be different if connected to a different "
"database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.server_version:1
msgid ""
"An integer representing the server version. See :pq:`PQserverVersion()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/objects.rst:49
msgid ""
"The number is formed by converting the major, minor, and revision numbers "
"into two-decimal-digit numbers and appending them together. Starting from "
"PostgreSQL 10 the minor version was dropped, so the second group of digits "
"is always 00. For example, version 9.3.5 is returned as 90305, version 10.2 "
"as 100002."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.full_protocol_version:1
msgid "An integer representing the server full protocol version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.full_protocol_version:3
msgid ""
"Return a value in the format described in :pq:`PQfullProtocolVersion()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.ConnectionInfo.full_protocol_version:5
msgid ""
"Only meaningful if the libpq used is version 18 or greater. If the version "
"is lesser than that, return the value reported by :pq:`PQprotocolVersion()` "
"(but in the same format as above, e.g. 30000 for version 3). You can use "
"`Capabilities.has_full_protocol_version()` to verify if the value can be "
"considered reliable."
msgstr ""

